{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JTiqhe32Pmok75DyEoy9Kf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that:\n1. The ec-spoke.local project doesn't have a `.spec-anchor` directory\n2. There is a `.codex` directory but not `.spec-anchor`\n\nThe user asked to follow `/spec-realign` procedure, but there's no SPEC-anchor project set up in the ec-spoke.local project. The spec-anchor CLI is available at `/home/kazuki/public_html/spec-anchor/.venv/bin/spec-anchor`.\n\nLet me check if there's a spec-anchor project somewhere else, or if the spec-anchor should be run against the ec-spoke.local docs directory.\n\n\nI should try running the spec-anchor CLI directly since neither project has a `.spec-anchor/config.toml` at the root, then look through the authentication and session-related documentation files to understand what needs to be aligned.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1917,"cache_read_input_tokens":39927,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1917},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5976bea-db53-4952-a093-280a919f4f68","uuid":"ed150c2e-1639-4ed1-bc6e-d05205d907d4","request_id":"req_011CbHrNv4TWmSHYTuyRqbvi"}
