{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01L6YjzhCd9ovMxWWYN3UWVM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I notice that:\n1. There's no `.spec-anchor/config.toml` in the ec-spoke.local project\n2. The spec-anchor CLI is at `/home/kazuki/public_html/spec-anchor/.venv/bin/spec-anchor`\n3. The relevant documentation about authentication is:\n   - 01_アーキテクチャ方針.md: Cookie session (Web) + Bearer token (API), separating customer/admin\n   - 04_未決定事項.md: Authentication base implementation is \"未確定\" (undecided): specific library/implementation\n   - 07_初期設計要件.md: Stateless principle - sessions to DB or Redis\n   - 04_未決定事項.md: No specific CSRF implementation mentioned\n\nI should try running the spec-anchor CLI to see what error occurs without a config file, and check if there's any CSRF-related documentation I'm missing. Since neither ec-spoke.local nor llm-helper has the spec-anchor initialized, I'll need to report that the project requires setup.\n\nLooking at the spec-realign template, there are four injection paths that run against the spec-anchor project: inject-search, inject-section, inject-chapters, inject-purpose, and inject-conflicts. Without a `.spec-anchor/config.toml` file, the CLI will fail, so let me test running these commands to see the actual error.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4426,"cache_read_input_tokens":41844,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4426},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5976bea-db53-4952-a093-280a919f4f68","uuid":"8903946c-9d35-4470-a24e-90aaf3e6c370","request_id":"req_011CbHrPZn6ei2KW9QBFwP9R"}
