{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HWw3VZZpxq1LMToUsS8rcn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both projects don't have a `.spec-anchor/config.toml`. According to the spec-realign template:\n\n> `.spec-anchor/config.toml not found under {root}` のとき → `spec-anchor-setup-project --target <project_root>` で project skeleton を初期化することを提案する (例: `spec-anchor-setup-project --target /path/to/project`)。`spec-anchor init` のような存在しない command を提案しない。answer の整形は実行しない旨を明示する。\n \nI need to report this error and suggest running `spec-anchor-setup-project --target /home/kazuki/public_html/ec-spoke.local` to initialize the project skeleton, while making clear that answer formatting won't be executed. But the user's actual question was about login session and state change request handling for the ec-spoke.local project—let me check if there's a spec-anchor setup elsewhere or if I'm looking at the right project root. to be related to work in progress. The user's memories include items about the ec-spoke.local project. The CLI error is definitive - there's no `.spec-anchor` setup.\n\nI should report the error properly according to the spec-realign error handling procedure. The spec says:\n- Report: `.spec-anchor/config.toml not found under {root}`\n- Suggest: `spec-anchor-setup-project --target <project_root>`\n- Do NOT suggest `spec-anchor init`\n- State that answer formatting cannot be executed\n\nHowever, I noticed the user is asking about \"認証セッションとCSRFの仕様\" - maybe they want me to answer based on the existing docs, even without spec-anchor? But the spec-realign procedure says I should stop and not format an answer when the config is not found.\n\nLet me follow the procedure strictly and report the issue.\n\nBut I should also check if there's a spec-anchor project at a different location that might cover the ec-spoke.local project - perhaps in a parent directory with the config.","signature":""}],"stop_reason