{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011XsxBgBQNkrA8MypzeH3JR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no `.spec-anchor` set up for the ec-spoke.local project. The spec-anchor CLI exists at `/home/kazuki/public_html/spec-anchor/.spec-anchor` but that's for the spec-anchor project itself.\n\nAccording to the spec-realign error handling procedure:\n> `.spec-anchor/config.toml not found under {root}` のとき → `spec-anchor-setup-project --target <project_root>` で project skeleton を初期化することを提案する\n\nI should report this error and suggest initializing the project. I should NOT format an answer.\n\n\nI'm reviewing the ec-spoke.local authentication documentation to understand the spec requirements—they cover authentication policies like cookie sessions for web and bearer tokens for apps, scalability considerations around session storage with Redis or databases, and several undecided areas including customer and admin authentication approaches.\n\nHowever, there are still open questions around API tokens, two-factor authentication, and password reset procedures, plus CSRF protection isn't explicitly specified in the documentation. I also notice the spec-anchor configuration file is missing, which means I need to stop here and report this issue rather than proceed with formatting an answer—I should suggest running the setup command to initialize the project properly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1903,"cache_read_input_tokens":48239,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1903},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5976bea-db53-4952-a093-280a919f4f68","uuid":"d7185ef0-0530-4d0a-bcaa-212610a7f3f8","request_id":"req_011CbHrSYPqRHLRSC2X4STwD"}
